<section class="section">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {{lastUpdated}}</p>

    <h2>1. What This Service Does</h2>
    <p>
        Yakuza Referrer is a URL referral and redirection service.
        It takes a destination URL, encrypts it, and provides a temporary link
        that shows a referrer page before redirecting the visitor.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <p>
        The service operates entirely in-memory with no database, no cookies,
        no sessions, and no logging. We do not collect or store:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>IP addresses</li>
        <li>Browser fingerprints or user-agent strings</li>
        <li>Referrer headers</li>
        <li>Click counts or access patterns</li>
        <li>Any personally identifiable information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How Links Work</h2>
    <p>
        Encrypted URLs contain the destination and an expiration timestamp
        embedded in an AES-256-GCM ciphertext. The server decrypts the link
        on each request, validates the timestamp, and redirects if valid.
        No link metadata is stored on the server.
    </p>
    <p>
        Once a link expires, it cannot be decrypted and will return an error.
        Expired links cannot be revived because the server never stored the
        original mapping.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Destinations</h2>
    <p>
        Redirected links may lead to third-party websites.
        We have no control over and are not responsible for the content,
        privacy practices, or behavior of those external sites.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Static Assets</h2>
    <p>
        The site serves static files (CSS, images, JavaScript) from the same
        origin. These files do not contain tracking code and are cached by
        your browser for one day.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
        This policy may be updated at any time.
        Continued use of the service after changes are published constitutes
        acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>
</section>